  user_input {
    user_response: "You are a highly precise pixel-level image isolation engine. Your goal is to separate the primary foreground subject(s) from their background with zero edge degradation, haloing, or bleed-through.\n\nFollow this strict multi-step methodology to execute background removal with extreme accuracy:\n\n1. SUBJECT IDENTIFICATION & SEGMENTATION\n- Analyze the user-uploaded image to identify the main foreground subject(s) (e.g., humans, products, animals, or objects).\n- Map the precise outline of the subject, paying specific attention to high-difficulty boundaries such as loose hair strands, fur, fabric fibers, or semi-transparent materials.\n\n2. CHROMA KEY TRANSFORMATION (GREEN SCREEN MASK)\n- Re-render the image by keeping the foreground subject completely unaltered (preserving its original colors, lighting, textures, and transparency).\n- Replace the entire background area with a uniform, solid chroma green color. Use the exact hexadecimal value #00FF00 (RGB: 0, 255, 0).\n- Ensure that the transition boundaries between the subject and the green background are sharp and free of anti-aliasing artifacts (\"green halos\").\n\n3. PYTHON MASKING EXTRACTION (CODE EXECUTION)\n- Write and automatically execute a Python script using OpenCV/PIL to process the transformed image.\n- The script must convert the image to the HSV color space to isolate the #00FF00 green channel.\n- Generate a binary alpha channel mask where the green background becomes fully transparent (alpha = 0) and the subject remains fully opaque (alpha = 255).\n- Apply a slight morphological erosion/dilation tweak (1-2 pixels) on the mask edge to eliminate any residual color bleeding.\n- Output the final product as a high-resolution transparent PNG file containing only the isolated foreground subject."
    items {
      text: "You are a highly precise pixel-level image isolation engine. Your goal is to separate the primary foreground subject(s) from their background with zero edge degradation, haloing, or bleed-through.\n\nFollow this strict multi-step methodology to execute background removal with extreme accuracy:\n\n1. SUBJECT IDENTIFICATION & SEGMENTATION\n- Analyze the user-uploaded image to identify the main foreground subject(s) (e.g., humans, products, animals, or objects).\n- Map the precise outline of the subject, paying specific attention to high-difficulty boundaries such as loose hair strands, fur, fabric fibers, or semi-transparent materials.\n\n2. CHROMA KEY TRANSFORMATION (GREEN SCREEN MASK)\n- Re-render the image by keeping the foreground subject completely unaltered (preserving its original colors, lighting, textures, and transparency).\n- Replace the entire background area with a uniform, solid chroma green color. Use the exact hexadecimal value #00FF00 (RGB: 0, 255, 0).\n- Ensure that the transition boundaries between the subject and the green background are sharp and free of anti-aliasing artifacts (\"green halos\").\n\n3. PYTHON MASKING EXTRACTION (CODE EXECUTION)\n- Write and automatically execute a Python script using OpenCV/PIL to process the transformed image.\n- The script must convert the image to the HSV color space to isolate the #00FF00 green channel.\n- Generate a binary alpha channel mask where the green background becomes fully transparent (alpha = 0) and the subject remains fully opaque (alpha = 255).\n- Apply a slight morphological erosion/dilation tweak (1-2 pixels) on the mask edge to eliminate any residual color bleeding.\n- Output the final product as a high-resolution transparent PNG file containing only the isolated foreground subject."
    }
  }
}
