  planner_response {
    thinking: "**Reviewing Compilation Success**\n\nThe compile was flawless, a total win on the initial attempt! I\'m now cross-referencing this successful build against the project\'s guidelines and goals to confirm that I\'ve maintained the integrity of each step. This includes a careful check to ensure the strictest implementation of the requested actions.\n\n\n**Refining Interface Elements**\n\nI\'ve streamlined the user interface down to a single dashboard, maintaining a clean title, upload field, and control panels as the core elements. The naming convention is also refined, with a straightforward \"Pixel-Level Image Isolation Engine\" for clarity. Furthermore, I\'ve secured all API calls server-side to adhere to environment constraints and API key security protocols.\n\n\n"
    modified_response: "I have designed and built a highly professional, interactive **Pixel-Level Image Isolation Engine** that provides a complete visual workspace for exact foreground separation. \n\nThe application implements your strict multi-step methodology through an elegant, photo-editor-inspired interface and a custom high-performance image processing pipeline.\n\n### \360\237\216\250 Visual & Design Concept\n- **Dark Creative Workspace Theme**: Styled in unified matte charcoal and deep obsidian tones reminiscent of expert-grade video editing suites, emphasizing visual focus on user uploads.\n- **Micro-interactions & Status Indicators**: High-contrast states, live pixel sliders, and active step trackers guide the workflow from upload to asset isolation.\n- **Double-Canvas Viewboards**: Interactive preview frame with a standard transparency checkerboard background to display results from original to green-screen masks and final isolated transparencies.\n\n---\n\n### \342\232\231\357\270\217 Core Modules and Architecture\n- **Step 1: AI Subject Vector Analysis**: Implements a dedicated server-side endpoint leveraging `gemini-3.5-flash` to query and dissect uploaded images, identifying the subject, edge color clashing metrics, outline complexity boundaries (low, medium, or high), and delivering custom extraction advice back to the workspace.\n- **Step 2: Chroma Key Green Screen Transformation**:\n  - **Dynamic Color Keyer**: Allows users to select any background shade on the original canvas with a precise **Color Dropper** click to automatically fill with exact `#00FF00` green-screen chroma values.\n  - **AI Green Screen (Gemini multi-subject)**: Integrated an optional automated fallback using `gemini-2.5-flash-image` on the backend to automatically map the subject and paint green screens with intelligence.\n- **Step 3: OpenCV-Equivalent Mask Extraction**:\n  - **Interactive Real-Time Preview**: Implemented equivalent, high-performance pixel-level custom matrix filters directly inside the browser using HTML5 Canvas to simulate the exact Python OpenCV operations (such as circular HSV color boundaries, morphological 2D grid erosion / dilation, and separable horizontal/vertical Gaussian edge-blur feathering) with instant rendering feedback.\n  - **Live Python Script Generator (`chroma_extract.py`)**: A code generation module that updates parameters dynamically. As you adjust your sliders (such as the erosion size or HSV range), the displayed Python script updates its numeric array definitions and code execution lines in real-time. This script can be copied or downloaded directly to execute the pipeline locally using native OpenCV (`cv2`) and PIL."
    thinking_duration {
      seconds: 1
      nanos: 510118137
    }
    stop_reason: STOP_REASON_STOP_PATTERN
  }
}
